## Quick picker
- Primary red: #dc2626 (bold, good for buttons)
- Soft red: #f87171 (backgrounds/badges)
- Deep red: #991b1b (accents, dark mode)

## Practical tips
- Tailwind example (set a primary brand color):
  ```js
  // tailwind.config.js
  const colors = require('tailwindcss/colors');

  module.exports = {
    theme: {
      extend: {
        colors: {
          primary: colors.red, // use Tailwind’s red scale (50–900)
        },
      },
    },
  };
  ```
  Use classes like bg-primary-600, text-primary-500, hover:bg-primary-700.

- CSS variables approach:
  ```css
  :root { --brand: #dc2626; }
  .btn { background: var(--brand); }
  ```

